sentence\": \"The study said that of the 1.6 billion AC units in use across the globe in 2016, more than half were in China (570 million) and the United States (375 million).\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2039, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alternating_current\", \"score\": 0.9967157643851633, \"rank\": 0.0032441627455342425, \"text\": \"AC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alternating_current\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alternating_current\"}, {\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998200739572344, \"rank\": 8.11711616239939e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The entire European Union had around 100 million.\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999991046025, \"rank\": 4.266871206369782e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics mark the most important stop on the athletic careers of the 10,500-plus athletes who will descend on Paris, which has led some high-profile countries to undercut environmental efforts for the sake of comfort.\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999310855424, \"rank\": 6.891437857219447e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a high-performance environment,\\\" Australian Olympic Committee spokesman Strath Gordon explained to The Post.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2474, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2520, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9233438763464377, \"rank\": 0.07271499441254285, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"___  APSummer Olympics: https://apnews.com/hub/2024-paris-olympic-games  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2760, \"entities\": []}]}"